        default void print(java.lang.String description)

        description - Message to be printed to console

      • getMethodName

        default java.lang.String getMethodName()
        See into the stacktrace and look for the fourth element in the stack, which is the function who calls the print function. Zeroth element in stack: The getStackTrace function, surprising but this is the case, involving multithreading First element in stack: The getMethodName function Second element in stack: The print function Third element in stack: the function calling the print function.
        Returns:
        The method name of the caller function, if called directly from a method body, then the caller of that caller will be returned
